Ångerman River.label: Ångerman River
Ångerman River.description: The Ångerman River is one of Sweden's longest rivers with a total length of 460 kilometers. It also has the third largest amount of water running through it, after Göta älv and Lule River. Wikipedia

Åsnen.label: Åsnen
Åsnen.description: Åsnen is a large lake in southern Småland, Sweden, roughly 150 km² in size. The river Mörrumsån flows south from Åsnen into the Baltic Sea. Wikipedia

Åre River.label: Öre River
Åre River.description: Öre River is a river in Sweden. Wikipedia

Öre River.label: Öre River
Öre River.description: Öre River is a river in Sweden. Wikipedia

Ösper.label: Ösper
Ösper.description: Ösper is a river of North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. Wikipedia

Öskjuvatn.label: Öskjuvatn
Öskjuvatn.description: Öskjuvatn is a lake in the Highlands of Iceland. Its surface area is about 11 km². With a depth of 217 m, it is the second deepest lake in Iceland after Jökulsárlón. Wikipedia

Üür River.label: Üür River
Üür River.description: The Üür River is a river in northeastern Khövsgöl, mainly in Tsagaan-Üür sum. The river is a tributary of the Eg River. Wikipedia

Černé jezero.label: Černé jezero
Černé jezero.description:
Černé jezero in the Bohemian Forest is the largest and deepest natural lake in the Czech Republic.
This triangular lake surrounded with spruce forest is located about 6 km northwest of Železná Ruda under a 300-metre-high cliff on Jezerní hora. Wikipedia

Śniardwy.label: Śniardwy
Śniardwy.description: Śniardwy is a lake in the Masurian Lake District of the Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, Poland. It is the largest lake in Poland with an area of 113.8 square kilometres. It is 22.1 kilometres long and 13.4 kilometres wide. Wikipedia

Ažytė.label: Ažytė
Ažytė.description: The Ažytė is a river of Kėdainiai district municipality, Kaunas County, central Lithuania. It flows for 20 kilometres and has a basin area of 98 km². Wikipedia

Aar (Lahn).label: Aar
Aar (Lahn).description: The Aar is a 60 km-long river in western Germany, left tributary of the Lahn. It rises in the Taunus mountains, near Taunusstein. It flows generally north through the towns Taunusstein, Bad Schwalbach, Aarbergen and Hahnstätten. Wikipedia

Acamarachi.label: Acamarachi
Acamarachi.description: Acamarachi, also known as Pili, is a stratovolcano located northeast of the volcanoes Aguas Calientes and Lascar, and southwest of the sector Salar de Pujsa of Los Flamencos National Reserve, in the Antofagasta Region of Chile. Wikipedia

Ablach (Danube).label: Ablach
Ablach (Danube).description: The Ablach is a right tributary of the Danube. It rises on the European Watershed, which is only a hint in this area, from the Mindersdorfer Aach in the municipality of Hohenfels in the Landkreis of Konstanz. Wikipedia

Acatenango.label: Acatenango
Acatenango.description: Acatenango is a stratovolcano in Guatemala, close to the city of Antigua. The volcano has two peaks, Pico Mayor and Yepocapa which is also known as Tres Hermanas. Wikipedia

Aasee (Bocholt).label: Aasee
Aasee (Bocholt).description: Aasee is a lake in Bocholt, Kreis Borken, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. At an elevation of 23.8 meter, its surface area is 0.32 km². Wikipedia

Adlerfels.label: Adler Fels Winery
Adlerfels.description: Adler Fels Winery is a California winery based in Sonoma that produces over 100 different wine labels in addition to production under its own Adler Fels brand. These include private labels for various restaurants, hotels and retailers. Wikipedia

Ach (Blau).label: Ach
Ach (Blau).description: The Ach is a river in Baden-Württemberg, Germany. Wikipedia

Achit Lake.label: Achit Lake
Achit Lake.description: Achit Lake is the largest freshwater lake in the Uvs Aimag of Mongolia, in the west of the country. At an elevation of 1,435 m above sea level it covers an area of 290 km². It is 28 km long, 16 km wide, and 10 m deep. Wikipedia

Aggenstein.label: Aggenstein
Aggenstein.description: Aggenstein is a mountain located on the border Bavaria, Germany and Tyrol, Austria. Wikipedia

Adolfosee.label: Adolfosee
Adolfosee.description: Adolfosee is a lake in North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. At an elevation of 39 m, its surface area is 0.307 km². Wikipedia

Agno River.label: Agno River
Agno River.description: Agno River is a river in the Philippine island of Luzon, in the province of Pangasinan. It is the fifth largest river system in the country with drainage area of 5,952 km². Wikipedia

Aich (river).label: Aich
Aich (river).description: The Aich is a river in Baden-Württemberg, Germany. It is approximately 29.7 kilometres long. It is located on the left tributary of the Neckar in Böblingen and Esslingen. Wikipedia

Aiguille du Jardin.label: Aiguille du Jardin
Aiguille du Jardin.description: The Aiguille du Jardin is a mountain in the Mont Blanc massif in Haute-Savoie, France. Wikipedia

Aibi Lake.label: Aibi Lake
Aibi Lake.description: Aibi Lake is a rift lake in north west China, near the border to Kazakhstan. Lying at the southeast end of the Dzungarian Gate, it is the catchment center of the southwestern part of the Dzungarian Basin. Wikipedia

Aiguilles du Diable.label: Aiguilles du Diable
Aiguilles du Diable.description: The Aiguilles du Diable is a mountain in the Mont Blanc Massif in Haute-Savoie, France. Wikipedia

Ailefroide.label: Ailefroide
Ailefroide.description: The Ailefroide is a mountain in the Massif des Écrins in the French Alps, and is the third highest peak in the Dauphiné Alps after the Barre des Écrins and La Meije. It lies at the south-western end of the Mont Pelvoux–Pic Sans Nom–Ailefroide ridge. Wikipedia

Aalkistensee.label: Aalkistensee
Aalkistensee.description: Aalkistensee is a lake in Kraichgau, Baden-Württemberg, Germany. At an elevation of ca 250 m, its surface area is 0.136 km². Wikipedia

Aiplspitz.label: Aiplspitz
Aiplspitz.description: Aiplspitz is a mountain of Bavaria, Germany. Wikipedia

Aisne (river).label: Aisne
Aisne (river).description: The Aisne is a river in northeastern France, left tributary of the river Oise. It gave its name to the French département Aisne. It was known in the Roman period as Axona. Wikipedia

Aire and Calder Navigation.label: Aire and Calder Navigation
Aire and Calder Navigation.description: The Aire and Calder Navigation is a river and canal system of the River Aire and the River Calder in the metropolitan county of West Yorkshire, England. Wikipedia

Akkajaure.label: Akkajaure
Akkajaure.description: Akkajaure is one of the largest reservoirs in Sweden. It lies at the headwaters of the Lule River in Norrbotten County, in Swedish Lappland, within the Stora Sjöfallet national park. Wikipedia

Štěchovice Reservoir.label: Štěchovice Reservoir
Štěchovice Reservoir.description: Štěchovice Reservoir is a dam on Vltava River built during 1937 - 1945 as the second stage of the Vltava Cascade. The dam is named after nearby village Štěchovice. Wikipedia

Aksu River (China).label: Aksu River
Aksu River (China).description: The Aksu River is a transboundary river in the Xinjiang province in China and Ak-Suu District of Issyk Kul Province of Kyrgyzstan. In Kyrgyzstan it is known as the Saryjaz River. The total length of the river is 282 km, of them 197 km in Kyrgyzstan. Wikipedia

Allner See.label: Allner See
Allner See.description: Allner See is a lake in Rhein-Sieg-Kreis, North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany. At an elevation of 63,5 m, its surface area is 0.10 km². Wikipedia

Alma River (Ukraine).label: Alma River
Alma River (Ukraine).description: The Alma is a small river in Crimea that flows into the Black Sea. Its mouth is located half-way between Yevpatoria and Sevastopol. Alma is the Crimean Tatar word for an "apple". Wikipedia

Alplersee.label: Alplersee
Alplersee.description:
Alplersee is a lake on the slopes of the Rophaien mountain near Riemenstalden and Sisikon in the Canton of Uri, Switzerland.
There is another lake in the canton of Uri with the same name near Unterschächen. Wikipedia

Alpspitze.label: Alpspitze
Alpspitze.description: Alpspitze is a mountain of Bavaria, Germany. At its base is the 'AlpspiX Viewing Platform', 2 curved metal walkways reaching out 13 metres over a cliff, crossing over each other, making the shape of an X. Wikipedia

Alte Elbe.label: Alte Elbe
Alte Elbe.description: Alte Elbe is a river of Saxony-Anhalt, Germany. Wikipedia

Altkönig.label: Altkönig
Altkönig.description:
Altkönig the third highest mountain of the Taunus range in Hesse, Germany, reaching 798 metres above sea level.
In the La Tène period around 400 BC, the Celts settled the Altkönig. They built a ringwall around the summit which is still evident. Wikipedia

Alte Oder.label: Alte Oder
Alte Oder.description: The name Alte Oder refers to an old branch of the Oder River in Brandenburg, Germany. Today it drains the Oderbruch basin, flowing northwards to the confluence with the Oder near Hohensaaten. Wikipedia

Amba Alagi.label: Amba Alagi
Amba Alagi.description: Amba Alagi is a mountain, or an amba, in northern Ethiopia. Located in the Debubawi Zone of the Tigray Region, Amba Alagi dominates the roadway that runs past it from the city of Mek'ele south to Maychew. Wikipedia

Ammer (Neckar).label: Ammer
Ammer (Neckar).description:
The Ammer is a small river in Baden-Württemberg, Germany, a tributary of the Neckar.
It has its source southwest of Herrenberg. Wikipedia

Antuco (volcano).label: Antuco
Antuco (volcano).description: Antuco Volcano is a stratovolcano located in the Bío Bío Region of Chile, near Sierra Velluda and on the shore of Laguna del Laja. Wikipedia

Amsoldingersee.label: Amsoldingersee
Amsoldingersee.description: Amsoldingersee is small lake adjacent to the town of Amsoldingen, in the Upper Gürbetal. It is located near the city of Thun, Switzerland. The lake has a surface area of 38 hectares and a maximum length of 1.1 km and width of 500 m. Wikipedia

Anaktuvuk River.label: Anaktuvuk River
Anaktuvuk River.description: The Anaktuvuk River is a river in Alaska's North Slope. One hundred and thirty-five miles long, it flows west from glaciers in the Endicott Mountains changing direction just north of Anaktuvuk Pass to ... Wikipedia

Arda (Maritsa).label: Arda
Arda (Maritsa).description: The Arda is a 290 km long river in Bulgaria and Greece. It is a tributary of the Maritsa. Its source lies in the Bulgarian Rhodope Mountains near the village Arda, part of the municipality of Smolyan. Wikipedia

Apfelstädt (Gera).label: Apfelstädt (Gera)
Apfelstädt (Gera).description: Apfelstädt (Gera) is a river of Thuringia, Germany. Wikipedia

Argazi Reservoir.label: Argazi Reservoir
Argazi Reservoir.description: Argazi Reservoir is a reservoir, created on the Miass River in Chelyabinsk Oblast in 1946. The Argazi Lake has become a part of the Argazi Reservoir ever since. The reservoir has a surface area of 102 km² and a water volume of 0,65 cubic km. Wikipedia

Arlesheimer See.label: Arlesheimer See
Arlesheimer See.description: Arlesheimer See is a lake in Baden-Württemberg, Germany. At an elevation of 212 m, its surface area is 0.060 km². Wikipedia

Armesberg.label: Armesberg
Armesberg.description: Armesberg is a mountain of Bavaria, Germany. Wikipedia

Arsenyevka River.label: Arsenyevka River
Arsenyevka River.description:
The Arsenyevka River is a left tributary of the Ussuri River in Anuchinsky and Yakovlevsky Districts of Primorsky Krai, Russia.
The length of river is approximately 294 kilometers and its basin area is 7,060 square kilometers. Wikipedia

Artillery Lake.label: Artillery Lake
Artillery Lake.description: Artillery Lake is a lake in the Northwest Territories, Canada about 20 miles east of Great Slave Lake. George Back reached it in 1834. Wikipedia

Assiniboine River.label: Assiniboine River
Assiniboine River.description: The Assiniboine River is a 1,070-kilometre river that runs through the prairies of Western Canada in Saskatchewan and Manitoba. It is a tributary of the Red River. Wikipedia

Atna Peaks.label: Atna Peaks
Atna Peaks.description: Atna Peaks is an eroded stratovolcano or shield volcano in the Wrangell Mountains of eastern Alaska. Wikipedia

Atta Cave.label: Atta Cave
Atta Cave.description: The Atta Cave or Attendorn Dripstone Cave in Attendorn is one of the largest and most beautiful dripstone caves in Germany. Wikipedia

Atzelberg.label: Atzelberg
Atzelberg.description: Atzelberg is a mountain of Hesse, Germany. Wikipedia

Aube (river).label: Aube
Aube (river).description:
The Aube is a river in France, right tributary of the Seine. It is 248 km long. The river gives its name to the Aube département.
Its source is in the Haute-Marne département, on the plateau of Langres, near the town Auberive. Wikipedia

Auersberg.label: Auersberg
Auersberg.description: Auersberg is a mountain of Saxony, southeastern Germany. Wikipedia

Auma (river).label: Auma
Auma (river).description: Auma is a river of Thuringia, Germany. Wikipedia
Source: Linda bei Neustadt an der Orla

Aurach (Regnitz, Mittelfranken).label: Aurach (Regnitz, Mittelfranken)
Aurach (Regnitz, Mittelfranken).description:
Aurach (Regnitz, Mittelfranken) is a river of Bavaria, Germany. It is a tributary of the river Regnitz.
The river Aurach starts in Frankenhöhe to the west of Klaus Aurach in the municipality of Markt Erlbach. Wikipedia

Ausa River.label: Ausa River
Ausa River.description: The Ausa River is a minor river some 17 kilometres in length which traverses part of northern San Marino and Emilia–Romagna in Italy. The source of the river is Monte Titano in central San Marino. Wikipedia

Ausangate.label: Ausangate
Ausangate.description:
Ausangate is a mountain of the Willkanuta mountain range in the Andes of Peru. With an altitude of 6,384 metres it is situated around 100 kilometres southeast of Cusco.
The mountain has significance in Incan mythology. Wikipedia

Avachinsky.label: Avachinsky
Avachinsky.description: Avachinsky is an active stratovolcano on the Kamchatka Peninsula in the far east of Russia. It lies within sight of the capital of Kamchatka Krai, Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky. Wikipedia

Aveyron (river).label: Aveyron
Aveyron (river).description:
The Aveyron is a 291 km long river in southern France, right tributary of the Tarn River. It rises in the southern Massif Central, near Sévérac-le-Château.
In 1855 evidence of prehistoric man was found near Bruniquel under a hill called Montastruc. Wikipedia

Awali (river).label: Awali
Awali (river).description: The Awali is a perennial river flowing in Southern Lebanon. In ancient times it was known as the River Asclepius. It is 48 kilometres long, originating from the Barouk mountain at a height of 1,492 metres and the Niha mountain. Wikipedia

Ayalon River.label: Ayalon River
Ayalon River.description: The Ayalon River is a perennial stream in Israel, originating in the Judean Hills and mouthing into the Yarkon River in the Tel Aviv area. The total length of Ayalon River is about 50 kilometres and it drains an area of 815 square kilometres. Wikipedia

Aydar Lake.label: Aydar Lake
Aydar Lake.description: The Aydar Lake is part of the man-made Aydar-Arnasay system of lakes, which covers an area of 4,000 square kilometres. This system includes 3 brackish water lakes located in the saline depressions of the south-eastern Kyzyl Kum. Wikipedia

Bárðarbunga.label: Bárðarbunga
Bárðarbunga.description: Bárðarbunga is an Icelandic stratovolcano, or subglacial volcano located under the ice cap of Vatnajökull glacier, rising to 2,009 metres above sea level, making it the second highest mountain in Iceland, ... Wikipedia

Bârsa River (Olt).label: Bârsa River
Bârsa River (Olt).description: The Bârsa River is a tributary of the Olt River in Romania. It starts at the junction of two headwaters Bârsa Groşetului and Bârsa Tămaşului. Wikipedia

Bärenstein (Ore Mountains).label: Bärenstein
Bärenstein (Ore Mountains).description: Bärenstein is a mountain of Saxony, southeastern Germany. Wikipedia

Bârlad River.label: Bârlad River
Bârlad River.description: The Bârlad is a river in eastern Romania, a tributary of the Siret River. Its total length is 207 kilometres. Its source is in the low hills between the Siret and Prut rivers, southwest of Iaşi. Wikipedia

Bălănești Hill.label: Bălănești Hill
Bălănești Hill.description: Bălănești Hill is the highest geographical point in Moldova, with an altitude of 430 m. It is located in Bălănești and belongs to Cornești Hills. Wikipedia

Bóbr.label: Eurasian beaver
Bóbr.description: The Eurasian beaver or European beaver is a species of beaver which was once widespread in Eurasia. It was hunted to near-extinction for both its fur and castoreum, and by 1900 only 1,200 beavers survived ... Wikipedia

Babia Góra.label: Babia Góra
Babia Góra.description: Babia Góra, or Babia hora, literally Old Wives' or Witches' Mountain, is a massif situated on the border between Poland and Slovakia in the Western Beskidy Mountains. Wikipedia

Baberowsee.label: Baberowsee
Baberowsee.description: Baberowsee is a lake in Brandenburg, Germany. It is located in Kagel, an Ortsteil of the municipality of Grünheide, Oder-Spree district. Wikipedia

Badacsony.label: Badacsony
Badacsony.description: Badacsony is the name of a region on the north shore of Lake Balaton in western Hungary, and a town in that region. The entire area is recognized for its wine, with vineyards dating back to Roman times. Wikipedia

Bachalpsee.label: Bachalpsee
Bachalpsee.description: Bachalpsee or Bachse is a lake with an area of 8.06 ha close to the First above Grindelwald in the Bernese Oberland, Switzerland. The lake, located at an elevation of 2,265 m, is split by a natural dam, the smaller part of the lake being 6 m lower. Wikipedia

Back River.label: Back River
Back River.description: The Back River, is a river in the Northwest Territories and Nunavut in Canada. It rises at an unnamed lake in the North Slave Region of the Northwest Territories and flows more than 974 kilometres mostly ... Wikipedia

Badener Höhe.label: Badener Höhe
Badener Höhe.description: Badener Höhe is a mountain of Baden-Württemberg, Germany. Wikipedia

Baekdu Mountain.label: Paektu Mountain
Baekdu Mountain.description: Baekdu, Paektu, or Changbai Mountain is an active volcano on the border between North Korea and China. At 2,744 m, it is the highest mountain of the Changbai and Baekdudaegan ranges. Wikipedia

Baker Lake (Washington).label: Baker Lake
Baker Lake (Washington).description: Baker Lake is a lake in northern Washington state in the United States. The lake is situated in the Mount Baker-Snoqualmie National Forest and Baker River valley southwest of North Cascades National ... Wikipedia

Baker River (Washington).label: Baker River
Baker River (Washington).description: The Baker River is an approximately 30-mile, southward-flowing tributary of the Skagit River in northwestern Washington in the United States. Wikipedia

Bala Lake.label: Bala Lake
Bala Lake.description: Bala Lake is a large lake in Gwynedd, Wales. It was the largest natural body of water in Wales prior to the level being raised by Thomas Telford to help support the flow of the Ellesmere Canal. Wikipedia

Bečva.label: Bečva
Bečva.description: The Bečva is a river in the Czech Republic. It is a left tributary of the river Morava. The Bečva is created by two source streams, the Northern Rožnovská Bečva and the Southern Vsetínská Bečva. Wikipedia

Bear River (Washington).label: Bear River
Bear River (Washington).description: The Bear River is a river in the U.S. state of Washington. Its upper reach is known as Bear Branch. Wikipedia

Behler See.label: Behler See
Behler See.description: The Behler See is a lake in the Holstein Switzerland region of North Germany. It lies between Timmdorf to the east and the town of Plön to the west. To the east it transitions into the Langensee, to the west into the Höftsee. Wikipedia

Beerenberg.label: Beerenberg
Beerenberg.description: Beerenberg is a 2,277 m stratovolcano which forms the northeastern end of the Norwegian island of Jan Mayen. It is the world's northernmost subaerial active volcano. Wikipedia

Beilstein (Spessart).label: Beilstein (Spessart)
Beilstein (Spessart).description: Beilstein is a mountain of Hesse, Germany. Wikipedia

Bei River.label: Bei River
Bei River.description:
Bei River is the northern tributary of the Pearl River in southern China. The other two main tributaries of the Pearl River are the Xijiang River and the Dongjiang River.
The Bei River is 63.34 kilometers long and located in northern Guangdong. Wikipedia
